

1. **"Indeed, with hardship comes ease."**
   — *Surah Ash-Sharh (94:6)*

2. **"And never give up hope of Allah’s mercy. Indeed, no one despairs of relief from Allah except the disbelieving people."**
   — *Surah Yusuf (12:87)*

3. **"So be patient. Indeed, the promise of Allah is truth."**
   — *Surah Ar-Rum (30:60)*

4. **"The strong believer is better and more beloved to Allah than the weak believer, while there is good in both."**
   — *Prophet Muhammad ﷺ*

5. **"Do not lose hope, nor be sad."**
   — *Surah Al-Imran (3:139)*

6. **"Trust in Allah, but tie your camel."**
   — *Prophet Muhammad ﷺ* (Meaning: Have faith but also take necessary actions)

7. **"Verily, after every difficulty, there is relief."**
   — *Surah Ash-Sharh (94:5-6)*

8. **"Whoever puts their trust in Allah, He will suffice him."**
   — *Quran 65:3*

9. **"The best among you are those who have the best manners and character."**
   — *Prophet Muhammad ﷺ*

10. **"Do not grieve, indeed Allah is with us."**
    — *Surah At-Tawbah (9:40)*
